snippet.textDisplay:
The first four lines are absolutely correct; however the second para has some modifications

Reedaha doesn't translate to "I love her"
Reed (need) aha (her)
so its actually "I need her"

so the more accurate translation will be:

Reed aha Reed aha (I need her, I need her)
Kefima reed aha (However it may be, I need her)
Teflatan ya halee (She is a young beauty)
Wil asaal reed aha (She is a honey, i need her)

Anti alhob (You are love)
Antilee alduna, anti lee aldunya. (You are the world to me, you are the world to me)


Reedaha Reedaha (I love her, I love her)
Kefima reedaha (However it may be, I love her)
Teflatan ya halee (She is a young beauty)
Wil asaal reegaha. (In her voice there is honey).
